Consists of introductory material and the eponymous work with a separate title page with the title The master highway plan for the Boston metropolitan area prepared for the Joint Board for the Metropolitan Master Highway Plan in cooperation with the Pubic Roads Administration, Federal Works Agency

A master ten year plan for Boston and twenty-three surrounding cities and towns; focuses on coordination between transit and highway planning and imposition of tolls to finance the project; includes results of traffic studies and estimates of future traffic volumes; makes recommendations for design of an expressway system, improvements to the street system, truck routes, and outlines parking considerations; includes cost estimates and many maps and illustrations
